00:46:04.050 --> 00:46:09.110
And he enumerates his
ailments and his infirmities

00:46:09.110 --> 00:46:10.550
and his deficiencies.

00:46:10.550 --> 00:46:17.300
And he says, to
young people, no.

00:46:17.300 --> 00:46:20.090
Eat, drink, and be merry.

00:46:20.090 --> 00:46:23.260
Know that-- and he's not
talking about debauch.

00:46:23.260 --> 00:46:25.910
He's talking about
living in the moment

00:46:25.910 --> 00:46:32.360
without a contemporary
obsession with things

00:46:32.360 --> 00:46:36.345
that if you were unlucky, will
land you at the age of 97.

00:46:41.910 --> 00:46:45.577
In closing, he said a very,
